12 amended to read:
13 7. Renewal Expiration and renewal of license; fees. Licenses Prior to January 1,
14 2026, licenses issued pursuant to this section expire 3 years from the date of issuance unless
15 revoked sooner. Beginning January 1, 2026, a taxidermist license entitles a person to
16 practice the art of taxidermy through the remainder of the calendar year in which the license
17 was issued plus 2 calendar years unless revoked sooner. A taxidermist whose license is
18 not suspended or revoked may renew the license every 3 years upon application by the
19 licensee accompanied by a $77 license fee.
20 Sec. 14. 12 MRSA §13068-A, sub-§14, as enacted by PL 2003, c. 655, Pt. B, §380
21 and affected by §422, is amended to read:
22 14. Operating motorboat in bathing swim areas. The following provisions apply
23 to operating a motorboat in a bathing swim area.
24 A. A person may not:
25 (1) Operate a motorboat within a bathing swim area marked or buoyed for bathing
26 swimming; or
27 (2) Operate an airmobile on a beach adjacent to a bathing swim area marked or
28 buoyed for bathing swimming.
29 B. The following penalties apply to violations of this subsection.
30 (1) A person who violates this subsection commits a civil violation for which a
31 fine of not less than $100 nor more than $500 may be adjudged.
32 (2) A person who violates this subsection after having been adjudicated as having
33 committed 3 or more civil violations under this Part within the previous 5-year
34 period commits a Class E crime.
35 SUMMARY
3366 This bill makes the following changes to the laws governing inland fisheries and
3377 wildlife.
38 1. It moves the laws governing the Fish and Wildlife Management Education Fund
39 into a subchapter dealing with specific dedicated funds.
Page 3 - 132LR0244(01)

1 2. It provides a mandatory hunting license suspension for a person convicted of
2 discharging archery equipment within 100 yards of a residential dwelling without owner
3 permission.
4 3. It removes the word "written" from the laws governing the moose permit lottery
5 application.
6 4. It repeals the prohibition on the use of a set bow for hunting.
7 5. It provides that if a person submits satisfactory evidence of having previously held
8 an adult license to trap in any other state, province or country, the person must also submit
9 proof of having successfully completed a trapper education course comparable to the type
10 described in law.
11 6. It provides that the laws governing the use of lead sinkers, bare lead jigs and painted
12 lead jigs apply within inland waters.
13 7. It adds 4 new wildlife management areas to the list of wildlife management areas
14 and removes one from that list.
15 8. It provides that, beginning on January 1, 2026, a taxidermist license entitles a person
16 to practice the art of taxidermy through the remainder of the calendar year in which the
17 license was issued plus 2 calendar years unless revoked sooner.
18 9. It changes the term "bathing area" to "swim area" in the laws governing motorboat
19 operation.
